x4freetext: A self-supporting 500 ug/cm2 foil of natural lithium
(92.5% of 7Li) was used as a target.
The angular distribution of the elastic scattering
was normalized to the OM cross-section at small
angles where the OM parameter uncertainties play only
The normalization error was smaller than 15%.
The same factor was used to normalize the angular
distributions for both elastic- and inelastic-
scattering data at the forward and backward angles
